This algorithm can also compute vector convolutions. For vectors $a = (a_0, dots, a_(n-1))$ and $b = (b_0, dots, b_(n-1))$, their convolution $c = (c_0, dots, c_(n-1))$ is:

$ c_j = sum_(k=0)^j a_k b_(j-k), quad j = 0,dots,n-1 $

